  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2 conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"4cb58e24-738d-4a7c-a645-d6fc8908b1bb\" data-macro-id=\"fdb527252146253819a1337a313aa0c65069875f26fbf998bdcd368637129bf8\" data-macro-name=\"include\"><style>[data-colorid=xn9y2m61zq]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=xn9y2m61zq]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=i36t5v8c86]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=i36t5v8c86]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=i6l0t31zrh]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=i6l0t31zrh]{color:#004eb3}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415588&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523329/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415588&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"611\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523345\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523329\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"8\" data-media-id=\"a88ad788-077a-42fb-8311-9602776eb4fe\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415588&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=611 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415588&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362 1x\" /></span><p>Welcome to RenderMan Fundamentals, the official introductory training for Pixar's flagship renderer.</p><p>This page contains everything you need to install and learn the basics of RenderMan.</p><hr /><h3 id=\"PxrSurfaceFundamentals-PxrSurfaceBasics\"><span data-colorid=\"xn9y2m61zq\">PxrSurface Basics</span></h3><p> </p><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"2e5edbbd-4bd0-4946-b864-f0c01ca97dfb\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-68279361\"><div id=\"expander-control-68279361\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Overview</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-68279361\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"70d3142d-12d3-4b73-bce4-e7b8d76dff05\" data-macro-id=\"665dfb87a26ed23d0b8d9659d665f4076116ea3acca4d710d1378eadd96587e0\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471524672\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This lesson will give you a fundamental overview of the amazing Uber shader that ships with RenderMan, PxrSurface</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"c7b3b7c3-b6c0-401a-9e8f-c40053f6cd14\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1301079039\"><div id=\"expander-control-1301079039\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Diffuse</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1301079039\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"c3bbb305-0279-45d8-bbcc-05bd858fb5e2\" data-macro-id=\"029554e95ffaa632756997a2116be1e04ea895565273a30b855de62f46f8e54b\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471529273\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, we'll explore how to correctly use the Diffuse lobe within the PxrSurface material and when to linearize your ACEScg or sRGB texture maps.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"f9eeeaa2-e749-4b01-a15f-16d9cf43a007\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1140710287\"><div id=\"expander-control-1140710287\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Artistic Specular</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1140710287\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"85fc92b9-6da1-4101-b8c1-be4b29fea3b9\" data-macro-id=\"7b2daf1261c43b94e1f371f563addb9785ff6daea85046d60675c3437317131b\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471550179\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>The first of two lessons about the Specular lobes in the PxrSurface. This lesson guides you through how to work in Artistic mode.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"bc71302e-b376-4d6f-86d8-92eb9497b8c8\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-732327450\"><div id=\"expander-control-732327450\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Physical Specular</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-732327450\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"1f7efea4-3efe-4e82-8491-efe0248e9b1a\" data-macro-id=\"bbbc055e9a6cc0eb02fb22108b84f0df1e86216358abaf5973689fdc7647c292\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471505659\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In the second lesson about the Specular lobes in the PxrSurface, we will be taking a look at the Physical mode and how you can use scientific values to create realistic metals.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"91b93be3-47de-4872-aff1-1d15b545003f\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-2045558714\"><div id=\"expander-control-2045558714\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Conductors &amp; Dielectrics</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-2045558714\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"10e9ab9b-f770-4b43-a3a6-c7b074e677cc\" data-macro-id=\"756aed6197f51a1a44dced32bf477ca75e976859a4880b87e591a83f3728db17\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471506695\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Understanding the difference between Conductive and Dielectric materials is essential in creating beautiful and realistic shaders. This lesson will give you all the fundamentals you need to know to get started.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"44b6722e-7558-4b1a-a02a-35495a141e32\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1684957069\"><div id=\"expander-control-1684957069\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Iridescence</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1684957069\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"47d92a70-8131-4204-91b8-6a9f8e91e2a0\" data-macro-id=\"71adea34a9ce91b07310bc1662b370f1e81156070cb2f9f49b61a8cab79e6c43\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471545420\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, we'll explore the Iridescence parameter and all the interesting ways you can use it</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"a0f4dc19-3cdd-42c0-b131-1bea33972f03\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1070195711\"><div id=\"expander-control-1070195711\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Velvet &amp; Fuzz</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1070195711\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"482e3c93-423f-4a9a-a6d6-c46f36d5c5f6\" data-macro-id=\"7e6f2b9bda4b720641d3b2f2e5d5b7a9afeeec2ad4aa0c881391f823cafe0a3b\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471533033\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn how to apply realism to your fabrics, plus how to use Fuzz to add dust and fine powder to your assets.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"613e6d37-a735-4024-a3eb-abc07791d2a8\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-104270773\"><div id=\"expander-control-104270773\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Glass</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-104270773\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"863361c7-f511-44a5-a46e-fc9d5fa2ef2f\" data-macro-id=\"8d8494781d1c22ea1da2e9c1ed31835a08cb0564281f642b6bde0aaae98ea068\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471535764\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this Glass lesson, you’ll learn all the fundamental parameters within the Glass lobe.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"c9dceeca-b9e1-4a26-ac94-cfd1fe8dc61b\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-65271277\"><div id=\"expander-control-65271277\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Glow</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-65271277\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"d29fdf29-81c1-4999-b92c-e4e01c8f08bd\" data-macro-id=\"1eea2d73b2e2b1f6381ff0d9c8a96857b4ebaa638857f81637737c32401c2fa0\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471541563\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This lesson is all about Glow and how you can use it within your scenes.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"8c932574-3f0c-44ad-8498-d23c62edecd9\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-389646801\"><div id=\"expander-control-389646801\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Subsurface Scattering</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-389646801\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"64508c76-05be-43d9-bda2-95256a7d86b1\" data-macro-id=\"368b20d85f4a2743578af8df1ab38c4cdd5311350e99e296d498bbb57dd31a9a\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521370674\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This lesson will introduce you to Subsurface Scattering in RenderMan and the various SSS models that ship with PxrSurface. Make sure you follow along with the project file!</p></div></div><p> </p><hr /><h3 id=\"PxrSurfaceFundamentals-PxrSurfaceLayering\"><span data-colorid=\"i6l0t31zrh\">PxrSurface Layering</span></h3><p> </p><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"1d46e88f-ddb3-4246-8562-4521ec41a534\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1158778743\"><div id=\"expander-control-1158778743\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\"> </span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Material Layering</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1158778743\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"d535a948-ae36-4982-850e-2a4223647dcc\" data-macro-id=\"96d35c59d19166895b435ef78ff96818877da24bd1d4c5ced3124dd84f2c09b1\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521400282\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, learn the basics of creating sophisticated layered materials with the versatile PxrLayerSurface material system. Make sure you download the <strong>Midnight Rebel</strong> Maya project to follow along!</p></div></div><hr /><h3 id=\"PxrSurfaceFundamentals-NextSteps\"><span data-colorid=\"i36t5v8c86\">Next Steps</span></h3><p>Now you’ve got the basics of how the PxrSurface material works, in the next lesson, we’ll take a look at the Material X Lama shading system from Industrial Light &amp; Magic.</p><p> </p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/599425025/R.F.+-+Color+Management\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599425025\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"previousLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415587&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523329/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415587&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523342\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"previousLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523329\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"8\" data-media-id=\"cb09d119-38a0-425a-9307-25d608cd5a22\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415587&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415587&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46 1x\" /></span></a><p> </p></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/600113153/R.F.+-+Materials+-+Lama\" data-linked-resource-id=\"600113153\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-right-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-right\" alt=\"nextLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415586&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523329/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415586&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523339\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"nextLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523329\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"8\" data-media-id=\"820f9835-b8a7-4b22-bb7e-3a7a82074582\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415586&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760415586&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46 1x\" /></span></a><p> </p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<hr /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png\" width=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523329/RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760416130&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;